                <p>
                    As a mental health counselor, I meet you with an understanding of what it is like to suffer. With this understanding I strive to help you find hope, healing, and ultimately wellness. I believe that every person wants to be their most authentic selves. I use evidence based and experimental techniques to meet my clients wherever they are in their journey of healing to stand by their side as they explore their barriers to wellness with kindness and compassion for themselves. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    My fondness of nature and my early work with tribal communities led me to specializing in nature-based therapy (NBT). Inviting nature into session gives clients access to a life-long healer that is always accessible, even after they have completed the counseling process. In a study by Meuwese et al., participants of NBT described nature being non-judgemental, reflecting change, growth, and inspiring curiosity. The participants felt that nature put their experiences into perspective and offered them comfort. Being in nature helped these study participants feel a sense of inner peace and interconnected to something greater than themselves (2021). Nature is an excellent companion to have on your journey to wellness, explore my offerings page to find more information.
                </p>
